(2, 767, 'Native Imaging', 'sales@nativeimaging.com', 'http://nativeimaging.com/', '65.33.133.27', '2013-07-28 22:15:00', '2013-07-29 03:15:00', 'Thank you for the article. Good to know that inline html can be inserted in the title fields, but this seems a bit too messy for clients. So, my assumption would be to add a custom field to the menu using php in the functions file to add a field wrapped with [data-icon]. I believe the walker function is the right way to go, but also considering building a small library of common words as identifiers for specific icons, which would reduce the amount of flexibility, but I''m looking for quick &amp; clean.  Thanx again.. :)', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.74):979663408', '', 0, 0),
(3, 767, 'Angela Holden', 'angelajholden@gmail.com', '', '76.113.148.153', '2013-07-29 07:16:00', '2013-07-29 12:16:00', 'Thanks for your comment! That''s a great suggestion and one I hadn''t thought of, although I did think this would be too much for a client to do on their own. I think based on a client''s business model, it might not be that hard to find a good selection of icons to include in the icon font and just make a key or map for the client when they want to change their menu. And at any point if they want icons added to the font, they can make the choice to pay the hourly rate for the work, or better yet, it''s something that could be included in a monthly service agreement. But honestly, it was the discovery of adding inline html to those titles that prompted my post. Everything after that is gravy. Cheers!', 0, '1', 'Disqus/1.1(2.74):980025118', '', 2, 0);
