(5, 1, '2013-03-15 20:26:30', '2013-03-16 01:26:30', '<h2>Website Design &amp; Front End Development</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WordPress websites that are highly customizable and allow you to control the content.</li>\r\n	<li>Static websites that don’t require dynamic or frequent content changes.</li>\r\n	<li>Splash pages or ‘Coming Soon’ landing pages.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nA content management system (CMS) like <a title="WordPress | Wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WordPress" target="_blank">WordPress</a> can have as many pages as you need as well as a blog. Your website may also have an image gallery, a calendar, and a contact form for email inquiries. It all depends on what you need and how your content should be presented.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<blockquote>“Poor design is like smog. You can see air only when it''s dirty. When it''s clean it''s invisible and you can see the fantastic mountains, unaware of the air at all. Design is like that.” –John McWade, Before and After Page Design</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Content Strategy</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title="Content Inventory | Wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Content_inventory" target="_blank">Content inventories</a> and audits for website redesign.</li>\r\n	<li>Proof reading content for spelling, punctuation, and grammar.</li>\r\n	<li>Revising and rewriting existing content.</li>\r\n	<li>Interviewing and researching to write new content.</li>\r\n	<li>Using <a title="A Closer Look at Hierarchy in Web Design | OnExtraPixel" href="http://www.onextrapixel.com/2010/06/24/a-closer-look-at-hierarchy-in-web-design/" target="_blank">hierarchy</a> and <a title="Information Architecture | Wikipedia" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_architecture" target="_blank">information architecture</a> to structure content on web pages.</li>\r\n	<li>Creating custom <a title="Taxonomies | Wordpress.org" href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Taxonomies" target="_blank">taxonomies</a> to categorize and organize content throughout a website.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nI’ve done graduate level research, writing, editing, and usability testing. I’m also a frequent blogger and I understand the impact of good content. Websites must be well written, organized, and provide a good <a title="10 Principles Of Effective Web Design | Smashing Magazine" href="http://uxdesign.smashingmagazine.com/2008/01/31/10-principles-of-effective-web-design/" target="_blank">user experience</a> (UX) so your audience can quickly find the information they need.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<blockquote style="text-align: center;">“Good, fast, or cheap… pick two.” –<a href="http://www.sixside.com/fast_good_cheap.asp" target="_blank">Old Adage</a></blockquote>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Design Tools &amp; Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HTML5</li>\r\n	<li>CSS &amp; CSS3</li>\r\n	<li>Responsive Web Design</li>\r\n	<li>WordPress</li>\r\n	<li>Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator &amp; InDesign</li>\r\n	<li>Color Theory</li>\r\n	<li>Typography</li>\r\n	<li>UX &amp; Usability Testing</li>\r\n	<li>Information Architecture</li>\r\n	<li>Content Strategy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDesign includes much more than software and applications. Good website design relies on a thorough knowledge of typography, content, and usability. Websites are words. If a website isn''t usable and doesn''t provide the information your audience needs, the design isn''t complete.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<blockquote>“…when a sentence is made stronger, it usually becomes shorter. Thus brevity is a by-product of vigor.” –William Strunk Jr., The Elements of Style</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2>Philosophy</h2>\r\nWhether you need a one-of-a-kind WordPress website, or you''d like to have an existing WordPress theme customized, I will always work hard to find the best, most cost effective solution for your needs. All of my custom designs are responsive and mobile ready, ensuring that your audience will always have access to your brand on any device.', 'Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'services', '', '', '2014-01-16 12:21:17', '2014-01-16 18:21:17', '', 0, 'http://angelajholden.com/ajh/?page_id=5', 0, 'page', '', 0),
