(1143, 1, '2014-02-04 06:49:16', '2014-02-04 12:49:16', 'This is a brief video explaining WordPress''s Custom Post Types. An out of the box installation of WordPress contains Posts, the default post type, and Pages. But these two things alone rarely meet the needs of every website. A good developer will make sure they understand your business and your audience before they pitch an idea or design to you.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nPosts should be thought of as dynamic like a blog, news feed, or any kind of content that gets updated regularly. Pages are meant for static content like your ''About'', ''Services'', or a ''Contact'' form. A web designer who understands where your content belongs on a website can use a platform like WordPress to create Custom Post Types.\r\n\r\n<figure><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/58Pp8vp-2ZU" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></figure>', 'An Overview of Custom Post Types', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'overview-custom-post-types', '', '', '2014-02-04 06:51:19', '2014-02-04 12:51:19', '', 0, 'http://angelajholden.com/?p=1143', 0, 'post', '', 0),
